\pard\tx720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0

\f1\b0\fs24 \cf0 <!$Scr_H::1><!$Scr_Ps::0>
\f0\fs28 The 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f3\b footer view
\f1\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f0\fs28  is the horizontal bar beneath the editor. It will contain slightly different controls depending on what is open in the editor.\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}When text is open in the editor, its word count is shown in the footer view. (You can change this to show the character count using Scrivener\'92s \'93Editing\'94 preferences, available from 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f3\b Scrivener > Preferences\'85
\f1\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f0\fs28  in the main menu.) Click on the word count for more information.\
\pard\tx940\tx1440\li1440\fi-1440\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl1\cf0 {\listtext	
\f5 \uc0\u8259 
\f0 	}
\f1\fs24 \cf3 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f4\i\b Tip #1:
\f1\i0\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f0\fs28  If the word count ever disappears from the footer view, it is most likely because you have switched on scriptwriting mode (see above).\
{\listtext	
\f5 \uc0\u8259 
\f0 	}
\f1\fs24 \cf3 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f4\i\b Tip #2:
\f1\i0\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f0\fs28  To see the word count of your entire draft, hover over the search field in the toolbar with your mouse. Doing so will display a count of all the words in the Draft folder (on the left) and a count of the words you have written in the current session (on the right).\
{\listtext	
\f5 \uc0\u8259 
\f0 	}
\f1\fs24 \cf3 <$Scr_Cs::2>
\f4\i\b Tip #3:
\f1\i0\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::2>
\f0\fs28  You can set a word or character count target for your manuscript via 
\f1\fs24 \cf2 <$Scr_Cs::1>
\f3\b Project > Show Project Targets
\f1\b0 \cf0 <!$Scr_Cs::1>
\f0\fs28 . (You can also set targets for individual documents by clicking on the target icon in the footer view.)\
\pard\tx220\tx720\li720\fi-720\sl264\slmult1\sa360\pardirnatural\partightenfactor0
\ls5\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\uc0\u8226 	}You can change the current text scale (zoom) using the percentage control on the left of the footer view. (This does not change the font size; it just zooms in and out of the document.)\
